# harness/reviewers.config — config-driven reviewer backend.
#
# Sourced by harness/review-task.sh. The reviewer is READ-ONLY and ADVISORY in every backend;
# switching backend is a CONFIG EDIT, not a code change (mirrors targets.config's per-prefix
# style: REVIEWER_BACKEND selects the ${BACKEND}_* keys; hyphens in the backend name map to
# underscores in the prefix, e.g. claude-fresh -> claude_fresh_).
#
# NON-NEGOTIABLE (do not "improve" this into a gate): findings are posted as a PLAIN PR COMMENT
# only — never `gh pr review --request-changes`, never a failing Check Run. A comment cannot change
# mergeability; that is what guarantees the reviewer can never silently become a gate once branch
# protection is enabled. The deterministic test suite is the sole merge authority.

REVIEWER_BACKEND="${REVIEWER_BACKEND:-ollama}" # ollama | claude-fresh | codex

# --- ollama (DEFAULT: local, free tokens, genuine model diversity; no tools at all = read-only) ---
ollama_MODEL="qwen3-coder:30b" # or qwen2.5-coder:14b (lighter/faster) — both present locally

# --- claude-fresh (minimum-viable structural separation: fresh CC context, restricted tools) ---
claude_fresh_MODEL="sonnet"
claude_fresh_ALLOWED_TOOLS="Read Grep Glob" # NO Bash/Write/Edit — mechanical read-only

# --- codex (cross-provider diversity; native --sandbox read-only) ---
codex_MODEL="gpt-5-codex"
codex_SANDBOX="read-only" # never workspace-write / danger-full-access

# --- the disposition adjudicator backend (config-driven; defaults to the reviewer's) --------------------
# review-task.sh adjudicates the reviewer's findings (CONFIRMED/REBUTTED) with a SECOND read-only pass.
# DISPOSITION_BACKEND selects that pass's backend from the SAME ${BACKEND}_* keys above (ollama | claude-
# fresh | codex). UNSET => it falls back to REVIEWER_BACKEND (one model to provision). RECOMMENDED: set a
# DIFFERENT model family than the reviewer when you have one — provider diversity reduces correlated blind
# spots (the adjudicator should not be the same model whose findings' cousins it is grading). Same read-only,
# advisory, NON-gating guarantees as the reviewer in every backend.
# DISPOSITION_BACKEND="codex"   # e.g. a cross-provider adjudicator for an ollama reviewer (uncomment to use)

# --- the Gate-A spec-review backend (config-driven; defaults to the reviewer's) -------------------------
# intake.sh `spec-review` spawns the read-only `spec-reviewer` against the DRAFT spec and CAPTURES its
# sentinel-JSON verdict (the Gate-A consensus oracle — closing the transcription trap). SPEC_REVIEW_BACKEND
# selects that pass's backend from the SAME ${BACKEND}_* keys above. UNSET => it falls back to
# REVIEWER_BACKEND (single config, shared default). Splittable: set it to tune the iterative spec-review loop
# independently of the final PR review — e.g. a cheaper local model for the loop, a frontier model for PR
# review (they ARE different agents/prompts). Same read-only, advisory guarantees in every backend.
# SPEC_REVIEW_BACKEND="ollama"   # uncomment to pin spec-review to a specific backend (else = REVIEWER_BACKEND)
